g.text: Reasons given by respondents who said they had not worn a facemask to protect
themselves from breathing in volcanic ash.
Don’t think I need to wear a mask
Don’t know where to get a mask from
Inconvenient to carry a mask around
Wearing a mask would make me too hot
Wearing a mask would affect my breathing
Wearing a mask creates humidity/ moisture
Noone else/few people wear a mask
Note: Respondents could select more than one reason.
Other reasons for not wearing a mask included the fact that they had not been provided with a mask, they use other things (like a handkerchief),
glasses get fogged up wearing a mask, don’t like wearing a mask, don’t go out much, or stay in until the ashfall ends.
Int J Disaster Risk Reduct. Author manuscript; available in PMC 2019 September 04.
